# Modal Edit Dialog Style

Use this structure and styling for Angular Material edit dialogs (e.g. TextVarEditDialog, FileEditDialog).

## HTML Structure

```html
<h2 mat-dialog-title style="color: #495057; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600;">{{ title }}</h2>
<div mat-dialog-content style="padding-top: 20px;">
  <mat-form-field appearance="outline" style="width: 100%; margin-bottom: 16px;">
    <mat-label>Label</mat-label>
    <input matInput [(ngModel)]="model.field">
  </mat-form-field>
  <!-- more fields -->
</div>
<div mat-dialog-actions align="end">
  <button mat-button mat-dialog-close>Отмена</button>
  <button mat-raised-button color="primary" [mat-dialog-close]="model" [disabled]="!isValid()">Сохранить</button>
</div>
```

## Layout Rules

| Element | Style |
|---------|-------|
| **Title** | `h2 mat-dialog-title`, `color: #495057`, `font-size: 18px`, `font-weight: 600` |
| **Content** | `mat-dialog-content`, `padding-top: 20px` |
| **Form fields** | `mat-form-field appearance="outline"`, `width: 100%`, `margin-bottom: 16px` |
| **Actions** | `mat-dialog-actions align="end"` |
| **Cancel** | `mat-button mat-dialog-close` |
| **Save** | `mat-raised-button color="primary"`, `[mat-dialog-close]="model"` |

